<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     1)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Critiques can be both <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     negative</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (e.g. your proportions are wrong) and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     positive</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (e.g. excellent job on the hair). Please feel free to use both.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     2)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;You suck! Quit drawing!&quot; is not a critique, it is a big step towards getting banned from this Board. This board exists to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     HELP</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> people develop their skills, not discourage them from drawing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     3)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> These forums are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>     not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> galleries. If you post here, expect to receive critiques on your work. Some may be negative. Remember, critiques are only opinions and whether or not you decide to further alter your artwork based on the feedback you receive from these forums is up to you. Bear this in mind when you post a reply.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     4)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Just saying &quot;Wow!&quot; with a smiley face isn't a critique. Try and explain why you liked the picture, or why you think it works. Any reply that seems pointless or vindictive runs the risk of being deleted. Again, we're not here to build (or tear down) egos, only improve artists.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     5)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Excessive and intentional thread bumping may get your thread locked or deleted. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     6)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Be sure to read the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm18.showMessage?topicID=2.topic">Rules and Regulations</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of the BBS in regards to content and conduct for the Board. If you are posting images of a &quot;mature&quot; nature, please provide a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    warning</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    link</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to the image. (i.e. do not use the image tags).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>     7)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Give credit where credit is due. If it's fan art, give the character's, serie's and artist's names with your post. If you've based your artwork from an existing image, post it as well. Don't rip people off.<br>
<br>
If you require further clarification of these, or any other of the Board's rules, please email us at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto: mods@polykarbon.com"> mods@polykarbon.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--><br>
